# Dwarapudi

Dwarapudi is a village in the Dr. B. R. Ambedkar Konaseema district of Andhra Pradesh. Dwarapudi is famous for its cattle market, cloths markets and Ayyapa temple. Dwarapudi is also known as Andhra Sabarimalai. Dwarapudi has its own train station.
Temples
On 20 March 2014 that Sri Venkateswara Swamy temple with gold coated sanctum sanctorum has  been inaugurated  in  Dwarapudi  Ayyappa Swamy temple on 19 March 2014.
